<plot>The film director, 'Carol Reed (I)' (qv), is the subject of this documentary short. The illegitimate son of the famous stage actor, 'Sir Herbert Beerbohm Tree' (qv), Reed was brilliant with actors, especially child actors, making him the perfect person to bring _Oliver! (1968)_ (qv) to the screen. Reed is best known for three films he made in the late 1940s, and the documentary offers generous clips from _Odd Man Out (1947)_ (qv), _The Fallen Idol (1948)_ (qv), and the most famous of all, _The Third Man (1949)_ (qv). The film director, 'John Boorman' (qv), the assistant director, 'Guy Hamilton (I)' (qv), the actors, 'Ron Moody' (qv) and 'Bryan Forbes' (qv) and the cinematographer, 'Oswald Morris' (qv), are among the interviewees.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?015797</url></doc>
